article.description: Hank Hollingsworth had 10 points, 11 rebounds -- both career highs -- and three blocked shots to help Cal Poly cruise to a 76-47 win over Division II Holy Names on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Hollingsworth leads Cal Poly to 76-47 win over Holy Names
article.linkText: Hollingsworth leads Cal Poly to 76-47 win over Holy Names
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Hank Hollingsworth had 10 points, 11 rebounds -- both career highs -- and three blocked shots to help Cal Poly cruise to a 76-47 win over Division II Holy Names on Wednesday night. Jakub Niziol had 12 points and seven rebounds and Marcellus Garrick and Victor Joseph scored 11 points apiece for Cal Poly (1-3). Niziol and Donovan Fields each hit a 3-pointer to spark a 12-2 run that made it 20-10 when Garrick converted a 4-point play midway through the first half. A dunk by Hollingsworth gave the Mustangs a 43-19 lead at the break and Holy Names never threatened. Kyvonte Davis, the only Hawks player to score in double figures, had 14 points on 6-of-13 shooting. The rest of the team combined to shoot 25.5 percent (14 of 55) from the field. The Mustangs outrebounded Holy Names 51-33 and scored 21 points off 13 Hawks turnovers.
